Two traffic officers have been arrested during a sting operation by the Hawks and the City of Joburg forensic investigation department. eNCA's Nqobile Madlala has more details. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Two traffic officers have been arrested during a sting operation by the Hawks and the City of Johannesburg forensic investigation department. READ: Driver's licence backlog | Are you insured without a licence? The suspects are alleged to have been selling fraudulent driver’s licences. Lucky Sindane from the Johannesburg Forensics Department says the suspects will be formally charged for fraud and corruption when they appear in court.